# v5-ASAMM Protocol -- Cursor Rules

## Project Context

This is the v5-ASAMM (Adaptive Sigmoid Automated Market Maker) protocol for Paxeer Network (Chain ID: 125). It uses an EIP-2535 Diamond Standard architecture with 12 facets, a sigmoid bonding curve, progressive fees, and an on-chain order book.

## Solidity

- Compiler: 0.8.27 with optimizer (200 runs) and viaIR enabled
- Zero external dependencies -- all Solidity is written from scratch (no OpenZeppelin, no Solmate)
- Source directory: `src/`
- All facets share a single `AppStorage` struct at a deterministic storage slot
- NatSpec comments required on all public/external functions
- 4-space indentation, 120-character line limit
- Custom `ReentrancyGuard` using EIP-1153 transient storage

## Architecture

- **Core facets** (`src/core/facets/`): SwapFacet, LiquidityFacet, PoolFacet, FeeFacet, OracleFacet, OraclePegFacet, OrderFacet, RewardFacet, FlashLoanFacet
- **Diamond infrastructure** (`src/core/diamond/`): Diamond proxy, DiamondCutFacet, DiamondLoupeFacet, OwnershipFacet, InitDiamond
- **Libraries** (`src/core/libraries/`): LibDiamond, LibPool, LibSwap, LibFee, LibOracle, LibOrder, LibReward, LibPosition, LibSecurity, LibTransfer
- **Periphery** (`src/periphery/`): Router, Quoter, PositionManager, OrderManager, PositionDescriptor, Multicall, SelfPermit
- **Tokens** (`src/tokens/`): Custom ERC-20, ERC-721, ERC-721Permit

## TypeScript

- 2-space indentation, single quotes, strict mode
- Test framework: Hardhat (Mocha/Chai) + Foundry
- SDK at `/sdk` -- typed ethers v6 client
- Indexer at `/indexer` -- Apollo GraphQL + PostgreSQL + Redis

## Testing

- Unit test every public function
- Fuzz critical math (FullMath, FixedPointMath, LibFee, LibSwap)
- Hardhat tests in `test/`, Foundry tests in `test/foundry/`

## Key Formulas

- Sigmoid curve: `P(x) = P_mid * (1 + k * tanh(a * x / L))`
- Progressive fee: `fee(x) = baseFee + impactFee * (x/L)^2`
- LP loyalty: `multiplier = time_factor * sqrt(volume_factor)`

## Network

- Paxeer Network, Chain ID 125
- RPC: `https://public-rpc.paxeer.app/rpc`
- Explorer: `https://paxscan.paxeer.app`

## Do Not

- Import external Solidity dependencies
- Modify `AppStorage` struct layout without considering storage compatibility
- Hardcode private keys or secrets
- Skip NatSpec documentation on public functions
